<subsection xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="subsec-additive-and-multiplicative-inverses">
<title>Additive and multiplicative inverses</title>
<p>Let z = <em>x</em>+i<em>y</em> be a complex number, then</p>
<p>
    <ol marker="i)">
        <li>
            <p>
                its additive inverse denoted by <m>(- z )</m> is given by : <m>-z = - ( x + iy) = - x - iy</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <p>
                its multiplicative inverse denoted by <m>z ^{-1}</m> is given by : <m>z^{-1} = \frac{1}{x + iy} = \frac{x}{x^{2} + y^{2}} - \frac{iy}{x^{2} + y^{2}}</m>.
            </p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</p>
<example>
    <statement>
        <p>
            Find the additive and multiplicative inverses of the complex number <m>z = 3 + 4i</m>.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <solution>
        <p>
            <m>z = 3 + 4i</m>.
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>i) -z = -3 - 4i</m>
        </p>
        <p>
            <m>ii) z^{-1} = \frac{1}{3 + 4i} = \frac{1}{3 + 4i} \cdot \frac{3 - 4i}{3 - 4i} = \frac{3}{25} - \frac{4i}{25}</m>.
        </p>
    </solution>
</example>

<exercise>
    <statement>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Verify that
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="a)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(\sqrt{2} - i) - i (1 - \sqrt{2i}) = -2i</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(2, -3)(-2, 1) = (-1, 8)</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(3, 1)(3, -1)(\frac{1}{5}, \frac{1}{10}) = (2, 1)</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(2 + 3i)^2 - (3i - 6) = 1+9i</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Show that
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="a)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>Re(iz) = -Im(z)</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>Im(iz) = Re(z)</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(z + 1)^{2} = z^{2} + 2z + 1</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Do the following operations and simplify your answer.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <ol marker="a)">
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>\frac{1 + 2i}{3 - 4i} + \frac{2 - i}{5i}</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>\frac{5i}{(1 - i)(2 - i)(3 - i)}</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>
                                    <m>(1 - i)^{3}</m>
                                </p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </p>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </statement>
</exercise>

